org.ilya.scheduler.schedule

Interface Schedule<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the elements stored in the schedule
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    NavigableDateSchedule

    public interface Schedule<T>
    Container for a schedule. It is responsible for executing requests, e.g. adding new items to the schedule, and for checking consistency of potential new items in the current state of the schedule. The schedule should check whether the type of the request is supported. The schedule interface if write-only, it makes no assumptions on how to retrieve the data.
